00:19:45.300 --> 00:19:47.250
AYELET OZ: I must
admit I don't know,

00:19:47.250 --> 00:19:49.770
so I don't want to
just make up things,

00:19:49.770 --> 00:19:52.770
but what we do see many
times and we're not

00:19:52.770 --> 00:19:56.520
going to get there, that the
reasons for why there isn't

00:19:56.520 --> 00:19:58.620
or there is no
crime are actually

00:19:58.620 --> 00:20:02.710
much wider than the
criminal justice system.

00:20:02.710 --> 00:20:06.990
So for example, if you
have a welfare state,

00:20:06.990 --> 00:20:09.640
the crime rates are lower, and
it's because of the welfare.

00:20:09.640 --> 00:20:12.736
It's not because of how much
people they put in prison.

00:20:12.736 --> 00:20:13.610
Yeah?

00:20:13.610 --> 00:20:18.200
AUDIENCE: I'm wondering about
