00:50:54.470 --> 00:50:57.480
I mean, for this person, I
guess it's really important,

00:50:57.480 --> 00:51:00.870
but when we look at it
as a policy question,

00:51:00.870 --> 00:51:03.650
I think this is what we
need to put our finger on.

00:51:03.650 --> 00:51:05.540
The open prison is
actually another thing

00:51:05.540 --> 00:51:06.830
that is just starting.

00:51:06.830 --> 00:51:11.060
It's really used
a lot in Europe,

00:51:11.060 --> 00:51:14.570
which we said one of the
main problems of prison

00:51:14.570 --> 00:51:17.150
as we know it is
that they isolate you

00:51:17.150 --> 00:51:19.537
from your community, from
your work, from everything.

00:51:19.537 --> 00:51:21.620
So what they're creating
now, and there's actually

00:51:21.620 --> 00:51:23.060
one going to be
created in Israel,

00:51:23.060 --> 00:51:26.130
it's building up right
now, is open prisons.

00:51:26.130 --> 00:51:29.210
So the idea is that, OK,
you need to serve your time,

00:51:29.210 --> 00:51:33.500
so you need to have some
restrictions on your liberty,

00:51:33.500 --> 00:51:37.080
but you don't necessarily need
to be isolated from everything.

00:51:37.080 --> 00:51:40.880
So what an open prison is,
it's usually, as you can see,

00:51:40.880 --> 00:51:42.380
here it's from from the UK.

00:51:42.380 --> 00:51:45.400
It's a nice little
neighborhood basically,

00:51:45.400 --> 00:51:48.200
and sometimes it will be
a building within a city

00:51:48.200 --> 00:51:51.890
or two buildings within a
city, that people are there.

00:51:51.890 --> 00:51:54.680
They need to be there
in certain hours.

00:51:54.680 --> 00:51:57.580
They need like their
entire daily agenda

00:51:57.580 --> 00:51:58.400
is set up for them.

00:51:58.400 --> 00:52:00.980
Like 4:00 in the morning,
you go, you have breakfast,

00:52:00.980 --> 00:52:03.930
you go to work, then you go
to therapy, then I don't know,

00:52:03.930 --> 00:52:05.930
you may have an hour off,
and then you come back

00:52:05.930 --> 00:52:07.880
and you sleep at the prison.

00:52:07.880 --> 00:52:11.270
But the idea is that
you can maintain

00:52:11.270 --> 00:52:13.900
some of your connections
to the community,

00:52:13.900 --> 00:52:17.000
again, so when you
finish your prison time,

00:52:17.000 --> 00:52:18.050
you have somewhere to go.

00:52:18.050 --> 00:52:19.990
So OK, you have your workplace.

00:52:19.990 --> 00:52:22.220
You've continued to
work the entire time.

00:52:22.220 --> 00:52:25.100
The idea is to try
to find a punishment

00:52:25.100 --> 00:52:28.370
that in some ways restricts
your liberty, and you know,

00:52:28.370 --> 00:52:30.680
none of us would want to go
and live in an open prison.

00:52:30.680 --> 00:52:32.060
It is punishment.

00:52:32.060 --> 00:52:34.550
But it does not have
all the bad influences

00:52:34.550 --> 00:52:35.990
that prison time has.

00:52:35.990 --> 00:52:37.590
And you say, well,
they can run away.

00:52:37.590 --> 00:52:41.960
The idea is that many
prisoners go out and come back

00:52:41.960 --> 00:52:43.280
and they go to vacations.

00:52:43.280 --> 00:52:45.950
Prisoners don't run that
much as you might think.

00:52:45.950 --> 00:52:50.300
Like you know the
teaspoon that you're

00:52:50.300 --> 00:52:54.290
carving your way to freedom,
that doesn't happen.

00:52:54.290 --> 00:52:58.100
Like most of the prisoners go
out to vacations, they go back.

00:52:58.100 --> 00:53:01.820
They know the price for not
coming back is enormous,

00:53:01.820 --> 00:53:03.470
and they figure
out, well, you know,

00:53:03.470 --> 00:53:08.390
I'd rather spend my prison time
and not sit another few years

00:53:08.390 --> 00:53:12.500
for an attempt to run away.

00:53:12.500 --> 00:53:14.850
And this is what the
open prisons are about.

00:53:14.850 --> 00:53:18.800
So yeah, people might run
away, but actually the chances

00:53:18.800 --> 00:53:21.860
are not very big, and the people
who go there to begin with

00:53:21.860 --> 00:53:24.570
are people with medium crimes.

00:53:24.570 --> 00:53:26.480
They're not very dangerous.

00:53:26.480 --> 00:53:29.290
So it actually works very well.

