00:55:22.756 --> 00:55:28.190
is declining, do we attribute
that to the Dorner community

00:55:28.190 --> 00:55:31.520
changes, or something else?

00:55:31.520 --> 00:55:34.550
AYELET OZ: It's actually not
due to the Dorner report,

00:55:34.550 --> 00:55:38.030
because we saw the
decline a bit earlier,

00:55:38.030 --> 00:55:41.300
and also the implementation
of the Dorner

00:55:41.300 --> 00:55:47.330
report in like everyday cases
is just in its beginning.

00:55:47.330 --> 00:55:48.740
It's actually a good question.

00:55:48.740 --> 00:55:52.430
Why we see one major reason
is because the crime rates

00:55:52.430 --> 00:55:53.360
are going down.

00:55:53.360 --> 00:55:56.030
Actually, the number of cases
are going down in Israel

00:55:56.030 --> 00:55:59.180
quite dramatically, so there
are just fewer prisoners

00:55:59.180 --> 00:56:00.650
because there are fewer cases.

00:56:00.650 --> 00:56:04.970
It's more about that than
about the Dorner report.

00:56:04.970 --> 00:56:06.835
AUDIENCE: Do we know why?

00:56:06.835 --> 00:56:09.210
AYELET OZ: Well, A, because
the crime rates are dropping.

00:56:09.210 --> 00:56:10.504
AUDIENCE: Yeah, why?

00:56:10.504 --> 00:56:11.920
AYELET OZ: Why is
a good question.

00:56:11.920 --> 00:56:15.110
There's not actually
a straight answer

00:56:15.110 --> 00:56:19.270
because it's also a global
trend of lower crime rates.

00:56:21.890 --> 00:56:28.260
It has to do with the
population getting a bit richer,

00:56:28.260 --> 00:56:32.870
meaning a lot of macro
explanations, none of them

00:56:32.870 --> 00:56:34.010
that we can be sure of.

00:56:34.010 --> 00:56:35.540
It's actually a
really good question

00:56:35.540 --> 00:56:36.914
why the crime
rates are dropping,

00:56:36.914 --> 00:56:39.050
because it's also
dropping worldwide.

00:56:39.050 --> 00:56:45.470
So trying to explain it with
one policy decision or other

00:56:45.470 --> 00:56:47.120
is probably wrong.

00:56:47.120 --> 00:56:48.290
We just know it happens.

00:56:48.290 --> 00:56:53.444
No one quite knows for sure
why it's dropping, but it is.

00:56:53.444 --> 00:56:55.110
AUDIENCE: OK, then a
different question.

00:56:55.110 --> 00:56:55.880
AYELET OZ: Yeah.

00:56:55.880 --> 00:56:57.530
AUDIENCE: You used
to have a blog.

00:56:57.530 --> 00:56:59.600
I was a big fan of it.

00:56:59.600 --> 00:57:01.656
You stopped updating the blog.

00:57:01.656 --> 00:57:03.240
What happened?

00:57:03.240 --> 00:57:07.790
AYELET OZ: Actually, I
forgot to pay my hosting

00:57:07.790 --> 00:57:09.770
and they deleted it.

00:57:09.770 --> 00:57:12.000
OK.

00:57:12.000 --> 00:57:12.860
AUDIENCE: Very sad.

00:57:12.860 --> 00:57:13.985
AYELET OZ: It was very sad.

00:57:13.985 --> 00:57:16.010
Actually, I also got
[INAUDIBLE] blog deleted

00:57:16.010 --> 00:57:19.820
because I forgot to pay
his hosting as well.

00:57:19.820 --> 00:57:21.710
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

00:57:21.710 --> 00:57:22.590
[LAUGHTER]

00:57:22.590 --> 00:57:35.290
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:57:35.290 --> 00:57:41.700
AUDIENCE: OK, so this
discussion takes into account

00:57:41.700 --> 00:57:44.620
that criminal rehabilitation
possibilities and everything.

00:57:44.620 --> 00:57:46.510
But I didn't hear
anything about society,

00:57:46.510 --> 00:57:48.990
which it expects of our justice
and especially the victims.

00:57:48.990 --> 00:57:51.340
I didn't hear the
word victim even once.

00:57:53.890 --> 00:57:56.480
What about their
need for justice

00:57:56.480 --> 00:57:59.220
and their need for
personal safety?

00:57:59.220 --> 00:58:03.920
If the grandma who
was robbed sees

00:58:03.920 --> 00:58:08.200
the one who robbed her getting
out or not even getting

00:58:08.200 --> 00:58:14.400
into prison, I mean, you
can tell her all that,

00:58:14.400 --> 00:58:18.600
but in many cases, she
won't want believe it.

00:58:18.600 --> 00:58:21.698
She won't trust the law
enforcement system anymore

00:58:21.698 --> 00:58:23.854
and might not report.

00:58:23.854 --> 00:58:26.020
AYELET OZ: I'll try and
answer, because the question

00:58:26.020 --> 00:58:30.730
of victims' rights movement
is actually a large question.

00:58:30.730 --> 00:58:31.940
I will say a few things.

00:58:31.940 --> 00:58:37.210
First, I think that the
most important places

00:58:37.210 --> 00:58:38.890
for the victims'
rights movements

00:58:38.890 --> 00:58:41.320
are actually in the
more severe sentences.

00:58:41.320 --> 00:58:43.470
It's not about the
short sentences,

00:58:43.470 --> 00:58:47.080
because as we say, in severe
violence, in the armed robbery,

00:58:47.080 --> 00:58:52.060
people would sit a long,
four or five years.

00:58:52.060 --> 00:58:55.990
In sex offenses, people
would sit a long time.

00:58:55.990 --> 00:59:00.340
And I think our need
to address the victims

00:59:00.340 --> 00:59:02.770
is most important
in these cases,

00:59:02.770 --> 00:59:05.830
in the cases in which
the crime created

00:59:05.830 --> 00:59:10.530
substantial trauma,
sometimes substantial risk

00:59:10.530 --> 00:59:13.160
or substantial harm
to the victims.

00:59:13.160 --> 00:59:16.420
And I think that in
many cases, actually,

00:59:16.420 --> 00:59:19.540
criminal law reform and victims'
rights would go hand in hand.

00:59:19.540 --> 00:59:23.050
For example, I would say
that the government needs

00:59:23.050 --> 00:59:25.030
to compensate victims' rights.

00:59:25.030 --> 00:59:26.800
For example, what's
happening now

00:59:26.800 --> 00:59:29.710
is that usually the
offender is said,

00:59:29.710 --> 00:59:36.670
OK, you need to compensate
the victim with the total,

00:59:36.670 --> 00:59:41.410
like the maximum for today is
256,000 shekels, and you know,

00:59:41.410 --> 00:59:44.150
if it's, let's say a rape
case, they would put it,

00:59:44.150 --> 00:59:50.560
OK, you need to pay 256,000
shekels, and he goes to prison

00:59:50.560 --> 00:59:52.780
and he's broke, and
the victim is never

00:59:52.780 --> 00:59:54.700
going to see this money.

00:59:54.700 --> 00:59:57.610
I mean, even if you turn
the rapist upside down

00:59:57.610 --> 01:00:00.230
and shake him, there will
be no money out of it

01:00:00.230 --> 01:00:01.600
because he has no money.

01:00:01.600 --> 01:00:06.040
And I think in a way,
putting the victim vis-a-vis

01:00:06.040 --> 01:00:11.140
the offender is a way the
government can walk away from,

01:00:11.140 --> 01:00:13.720
and I think we
need to compensate

01:00:13.720 --> 01:00:15.910
by the government the victims.

01:00:15.910 --> 01:00:18.280
AUDIENCE: The victim
doesn't want the money.

01:00:18.280 --> 01:00:21.280
The victims want to see
the criminal suffer.

01:00:21.280 --> 01:00:22.580
AYELET OZ: Let me answer.

01:00:22.580 --> 01:00:23.380
No, this is

01:00:23.380 --> 01:00:24.210
AUDIENCE: That's why
we punish people.

01:00:24.210 --> 01:00:24.910
AYELET OZ: NO.

01:00:24.910 --> 01:00:25.540
Another thing.

01:00:25.540 --> 01:00:26.170
No.

01:00:26.170 --> 01:00:27.095
AUDIENCE: They want retaliation.

01:00:27.095 --> 01:00:27.970
That's the original--

01:00:27.970 --> 01:00:29.500
AYELET OZ: No.

01:00:29.500 --> 01:00:32.860
Yeah, but the thing is that
studies and discussions

01:00:32.860 --> 01:00:37.030
with victims showed that
victims are many people

01:00:37.030 --> 01:00:39.130
and victims want many things.

01:00:39.130 --> 01:00:41.840
Some victims want to
see the offender suffer.

01:00:41.840 --> 01:00:43.750
They want them never
to go out of prison.

01:00:43.750 --> 01:00:45.550
There are some victims.

01:00:45.550 --> 01:00:52.830
Other victims do what we call
I forgot the English term,

01:00:52.830 --> 01:00:55.810
but the idea is that
they meet their offender,

01:00:55.810 --> 01:00:59.960
and what they want is their
offender to say, I'm sorry.

01:00:59.960 --> 01:01:04.000
And what they want is some
kind of acknowledgment

01:01:04.000 --> 01:01:05.720
of what was done to them.

01:01:05.720 --> 01:01:07.870
And there are actually
these arenas in which

01:01:07.870 --> 01:01:10.450
offender and victim can meet.

01:01:10.450 --> 01:01:12.970
It's done in therapy and
so on, so it's not like,

01:01:12.970 --> 01:01:14.890
oh, go meet them somewhere.

01:01:14.890 --> 01:01:18.919
And the offender says, I now
acknowledge what I did to you,

01:01:18.919 --> 01:01:20.960
and I am sorry, and I will
try to make it better.

01:01:20.960 --> 01:01:24.790
And we have a lot of victims
saying, this meant more to me.

01:01:24.790 --> 01:01:27.280
And we actually have
this, it's a kind

01:01:27.280 --> 01:01:31.780
of a well known story of
this woman who was actually

01:01:31.780 --> 01:01:34.870
beaten very hard,
and then like, I

01:01:34.870 --> 01:01:36.980
think she had like a
head injury or something,

01:01:36.980 --> 01:01:38.290
something really serious.

01:01:38.290 --> 01:01:43.000
And she goes and she meets this
young man who did this to her,

01:01:43.000 --> 01:01:46.870
and she actually understands
how for him, it actually

01:01:46.870 --> 01:01:47.870
changed his entire life.

01:01:47.870 --> 01:01:50.810
He got like 15 years in
prison or something like that.

01:01:50.810 --> 01:01:55.920
And she goes and she meets him,
and he sees what he did to her

01:01:55.920 --> 01:01:58.140
and acknowledges
what he did to her.

01:01:58.140 --> 01:02:03.460
And she actually like kind
of keeps in touch with him

01:02:03.460 --> 01:02:06.670
while he's in prison,
and this gives him

01:02:06.670 --> 01:02:11.860
a sense of meaning that
he somehow managed,

01:02:11.860 --> 01:02:15.040
not to make right but to
acknowledge what he did,

01:02:15.040 --> 01:02:18.170
and she feels that she
has some kind of meaning.

01:02:18.170 --> 01:02:20.890
And this sense of meaning,
and actually yes, money, money

01:02:20.890 --> 01:02:24.280
to pay for therapy, money
to pay for a lot of things

01:02:24.280 --> 01:02:26.420
that many time victims want.

01:02:26.420 --> 01:02:30.596
And some of the victims
want nothing to do.

01:02:30.596 --> 01:02:31.720
They don't want to hear it.

01:02:31.720 --> 01:02:33.550
They just want to move
on with their lives,

01:02:33.550 --> 01:02:35.620
and actually, when
you actually talk

01:02:35.620 --> 01:02:39.100
to victims or with
advocates of victims,

01:02:39.100 --> 01:02:40.840
you see victims
want lots of things.

01:02:40.840 --> 01:02:43.120
And there was
actually a few cases

01:02:43.120 --> 01:02:46.282
in which like, you know,
the prosecution says, well,

01:02:46.282 --> 01:02:48.490
you need to send him to a
long time in prison because

01:02:48.490 --> 01:02:49.030
of the victim.

01:02:49.030 --> 01:02:51.321
And the victim says, I don't
care if he goes to prison.

01:02:51.321 --> 01:02:53.690
I just want to move
on with my life.

01:02:53.690 --> 01:02:56.500
So trying to speak in
the name of victims

01:02:56.500 --> 01:03:03.100
and assume what victims want is
something I really don't like.

01:03:03.100 --> 01:03:06.100
I think that we need to listen
to victims and what they want,

01:03:06.100 --> 01:03:09.280
and I think that in
many times, actually

01:03:09.280 --> 01:03:13.570
the defendant's rights and
victim's rights would go hand

01:03:13.570 --> 01:03:17.410
in hand, because in a
way, they are the two

01:03:17.410 --> 01:03:22.500
humans in the system, and
many times, looking at them

01:03:22.500 --> 01:03:26.010
and what they need
and what they think

01:03:26.010 --> 01:03:29.480
would make them make
different decisions than what

01:03:29.480 --> 01:03:31.393
the system would decide.

01:03:31.393 --> 01:03:40.970
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]
Criminal punishment

01:03:40.970 --> 01:03:44.180
would still be there, and it
would serve in the future,

01:03:44.180 --> 01:03:46.420
if he comes back and
do the same thing

01:03:46.420 --> 01:03:49.950
for some reason, the
only thing that changes

01:03:49.950 --> 01:03:51.470
is the actual punishment.

01:03:51.470 --> 01:03:54.142
It's not the conviction itself.

01:03:54.142 --> 01:03:56.100
AYELET OZ: But also, as
I said, victims' rights

01:03:56.100 --> 01:03:59.760
are mostly relevant to the
really harsher crimes, which

01:03:59.760 --> 01:04:03.750
are actually a different
talk than the shorter prison

01:04:03.750 --> 01:04:06.367
sentence that usually
have no victim.

01:04:06.367 --> 01:04:08.700
For example, like in a drug
offense, there is no victim.

01:04:08.700 --> 01:04:11.460
It's wrong, and we've put
people in prison for it,

01:04:11.460 --> 01:04:12.650
but there is no victim.

01:04:12.650 --> 01:04:14.263
No one is actually hurt.

01:04:23.787 --> 01:04:25.370
SPEAKER 1: So thank
you you very much.

01:04:25.370 --> 01:04:27.974
Actually, it was quite
fascinating for me to see.

01:04:27.974 --> 01:04:29.390
I didn't think
about it in advance

01:04:29.390 --> 01:04:33.030
that Googlers are engineers,
and they think numbers.

01:04:33.030 --> 01:04:36.820
And we had many project
managers who will automatically

01:04:36.820 --> 01:04:39.420
say, how do we optimize
the system, what

01:04:39.420 --> 01:04:40.410
are the flaws here.

01:04:40.410 --> 01:04:41.790
It was very interesting to me.

01:04:41.790 --> 01:04:43.840
So thank you very much.

